 surname <i>Harris</i> may possibly also originate from a transferred use of the Greek personal (given) name <i>Charis</i> or <i>Harris</i> (shortened forms of <i>Charalampos</i>) as a surname (i.e. as a replacement of the original surname).","Americanized form of various like-sounding Jewish surnames."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Màiri ."],"variants":[{"name":"Màiri","meanings":["Gaelic equivalent of <b>Mary</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Herries was born about 1440, in Roxburgh, Roxburghshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. She married Sir Archibald Douglas 3rd Lord of Cavers about 1460, in Roxburgh, Roxburghshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 2 daughters."},"et":{"about 1440–":"umbes 1440–Surnud","1424–1486":"1424–1486","1445–1486":"1445–1486","1448–Male":"1448–Surnud","1450–1506":"1450–1506","1450–Female":"1450–Surnud","1440–Female":"1440–Surnud","Abt 1450":"umbes 1450","1448":"1448","1424":"1424","1445":"1445","1486":"1486","1440":"1440","1450":"1450","abt 1450":"umbes 1450","about 1440":"umbes 1440","1506":"1506","about 1460":"umbes 1460","Abt 1448":"umbes 1448","Teviotdale, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Teviotdale, Roxburghshire, Scotland",", Roxburgh, Scotland":"Roxburgh, Roxburghshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Roxburgh, Scotland":"Roxburgh, Roxburghshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Atholl, Angus, Scotland":"Atholl, Perth and Kinross, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Mochrum, Wigtownshire, Scotland":"Mochrum, Wigtownshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Cavers, Roxburgh, Scotland":"Cavers, Roxburghshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1440–":"noin 1440–Kuollut","1424–1486":"1424–1486","1445–1486":"1445–1486","1448–Male":"1448–Kuollut","1450–1506":"1450–1506","1450–Female":"1450–Kuollut","1440–Female":"1440–Kuollut","Abt 1450":"noin 1450","1448":"1448","1424":"1424","1445":"1445","1486":"1486","1440":"1440